LAGOS – After a thrilling fight to win the World Boxing Federation (WBF) Interna­tional Super Featherweight title on December 27, Nige­rian Ridwan ”Scorpion” Oyekola has emerged the WBF Boxer of the Month for December 2020. Oyekola, the Internation­al Boxing Federation (IBF) Featherweight Champion also won the prestigious ‘New­comer of The Year’ award according to an official state­ment released on the WBF website over the weekend. “Oyekola showed his great potential with an outstanding win over the Argentinean Lucas Mattias Montesino on December 27 in the fight of the year. Look out for great things in 2021 for this young fighter with huge potential”, the statement reads in part. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Some of the previous winners of the award in­cludes: Donald Brown (USA) / Ayumu Hanada (Japan) 2019, Oluwaseun Joshua Wahab (Nigeria) 2018, Sher­if Morina (Germany) 2017, Malik Zinad (Libya) & An­dré Valavanis (Egypt) 2016, and Frans Ramabola (South Africa) who won it in 2015. Oyekola beat Argentina´s Montesino by unanimous decision, in what was called a clear-cut fight of the year candidate by WBF President Howard Goldberg. ‘I Am Still Alive’ –Christian Chukwu NPFL: Plateau United Record First Win Only 23-years old, Oye­kola who was celebrated on the official website of the boxing body took his record to 7-1-1 (5) while cap­turing his first internation­al title, but there is certain­ly much more to come from this promising young man in the future according to WBF President.